The paper deals with the computational complexity of the knapsack problem and its variants, which are classic topics in computer science. The paper specifically focuses on the fixed-parameter tractability and kernelization of these problems, which are topics that fall under the categories of data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the connection of parameterized knapsack problems to linear programming (cs.GT) and approximation algorithms (cs.LG).
